A Proud Past and a Solid Future
This slogan was selected from a contest held among McJunkin employees in 1971 when the company was celebrating its 50th year in business. In 1977 Lew Ketchum, a Delaware Indian, turned a dream into reality when he founded Red Man Pipe & Supply Co., the nation’s only full-service, minority-owned oil field supply company. On November 1, 2007 McJunkin Corporation and Red Man Pipe & Supply Company merged to form, what is now, MRC Global. The history of our new company continues to develop daily.
Launch the Company Timeline below to learn more about the history of MRC Global.




